description:
We are looking for **Permit Specialists** in the Engineering Department to manage and coordinate all aspects of the permitting process for telecommunications infrastructure projects.


The Permit Specialist as a key member of our engineering department, will contribute to the success of our initiatives by permitting, overseeing the permit process, and facilitating efficient project execution.

**Responsibilities**:

* Anticipate and schedule permits to avoid project roadblocks;
* Facilitate resolution of issues as they arise to keep the project on schedule;
* Research and gather data to support project team scheduling requirements;
* Serve as liaison with internal resources to ensure permit applications are submitted in order and on time to meet the project schedule;
* Provide follow-up to pending issues to ensure completion of tasks – internal and external;
* Coordinate with permitting agencies to organize applications, adjust as desired, and resolve any issues preventing or delaying the permitting process;
* Develop plans including timelines, tasks, and schedules for permits from inception through issuance;
* Ensure permit submittal packages are following jurisdictional requirements;
* Identify jurisdiction-specific requirements and provide that information to the team;
* Monitor/track permit packages via online systems, email, or in person as necessary to meet local requirements;
* Monitor project folders and effectively communicate the status of each permit.

**Requirements**

* Bachelor's degree in a relevant field (e.g., engineering, environmental science, urban planning);
* A minimum of 2 years of proven experience as a permit specialist in the utilities industry;
* Knowledge of utility regulations, codes, and standards;
* Proficiency in using software tools for tracking and managing permits;
* Ability to travel within the market if required.

**Benefits**

* Great Work Environment;
* Competitive Payment;
* Paid weekly - each Friday;
* Possibility to work remotely;
* Career Advancement Opportunities.
